  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0db8 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "American school shootings peak",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to a 31-page report released by the National Center for Education, there have been 93 school shootings during the past school year, including 43 school shootings and 50 school shootings with injuries.",
        "In addition, 53 school shootings were reported during the school year without any casualties. Only 23 school shootings and injuries were reported during the 2000-01 school year.",
        "Although the rate of non-fatal (only injuries) school violence for children aged 12 to 18 is lower in 2019 than in 2009, the number of school shootings injured in 2021 is higher than any other year since data collection began in the early 2000s. It has increased from 11 in 2009 to 93 in 2021, \u201dsaid Peggy G. Kerr, commissioner of the U.S. National Center for Education Statistics, in a news release."
      ],
